Vekol-TTS — ckb edge
Built by Darvan Shvan · © Revge

This model is a derivative work built on:

1. Meta MMS-TTS (facebook/mms-tts-kmr-script_arabic)
   - Base model that was fine-tuned.
   - License: CC-BY-NC 4.0  (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/)

2. Vekol server TTS (Revge) — built on Coqui XTTS-v2
   - Revge's higher-quality server TTS model, used as the teacher to generate
     the distillation training audio for this edge model.
   - It is built on Coqui XTTS-v2, licensed under the Coqui Public Model License
     (CPML), non-commercial (https://coqui.ai/cpml) — so audio it produces, and
     models distilled from it, carry CPML / non-commercial terms.

Because both upstream components are NON-COMMERCIAL, this derivative is released
under CC-BY-NC 4.0 and must NOT be used commercially. For commercial use, retrain
from a permissively-licensed base (e.g. a from-scratch VITS / Piper).

Training data: a private Sorani speech corpus (Revge) + audio distilled from the
Vekol server (XTTS-based) teacher. The shipped edge model contains learned
weights only (no XTTS code or weights; it runs standalone via ONNX).
